text: Abulyaisovo (, ) is a rural locality (a village) in Abulyaisovsky Selsoviet, Zianchurinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 265 as of 2010. There are 10 streets. == Geography == The village is located 64 km from Isyangulovo and 4 km from Malinovka. == Ethnicity == The village is inhabited by Bashkirs. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zianchurinsky District
title: Abulyaisovo
